{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/0210AuthFlowChange","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/atprotokit\/0210authflowchange"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn about how to set up your project with the new authentication flow changes."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"With the release of 0.26.0 comes a new migration flow for ATProtoKit developers. This change is fairly small, but this article will still cover what to expect in order to clear any confusion.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Authentication Flow","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Authentication-Flow"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Previously, when you wanted to authenticate to an AT Protocol service, you used an initializer from "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference"},{"text":", which contained the ","type":"text"},{"code":"handle","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"password","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" parameters. Then, you would use ATProtocolConfiguration.authenticate(authenticationFactorToken:) and passed the instance to the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration(handle: example.bsky.social, password: hunter2)","","Task {","    do {","        \/\/ You can put it in here…","        try await config.authenticate()","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Or here…","        try await config.authenticate()","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"With version 0.26, this has been changed slightly:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration()","","Task {","    do {","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Enter the handle and password in here.","        try await config.authenticate(","            handle: example.bsky.social,","            password: hunter2","        )","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Here are the changes being made:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":"’s initializer no longer takes the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handle"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"password"},{"text":" parameters: now, ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is responsible."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the only external change. However, more has been made internally:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSession"},{"type":"text","text":" is no longer stored inside of "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":": now, a new "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":" named "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSessionRegistry"},{"type":"text","text":" holds all instances of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"struct"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UUID"},{"type":"text","text":" value has been added to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". This value is linked to all objects that are related to the session. This is part of the new initializer for ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" now closely follows "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SessionConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":". In fact, the following methods are no longer stored in the "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", but have moved to default implementations of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/getSession()","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/refreshSession()","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/deleteSession()","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A new ","type":"text"},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":", will now manage the management of the password, access token, and refresh token. An "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain"},{"text":" is available for applications running on Apple’s platforms.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"SessionConfiguration","text":"`SessionConfiguration`","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As mentioned previously, "},{"code":"SessionConfiguration","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" now has default configurations for each of the required methods. It is also ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"text":" and requires a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":" to conform to it. The default implementation assumes you’re using an App Password to authenticate by default, but you’re able to create new implementations for your own conforming ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Furthermore, the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)-272a8","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" method handles Two-Factor Authentication, but the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"text":" can also handle OAuth. This is thanks to a ","type":"text"},{"code":"AsyncStream","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"-related properties, named ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeContinuation","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"anchor":"Auto-managing-the-Keychain","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Auto-managing the Keychain"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As mentioned earlier, a new "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" have been made: "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain"},{"type":"text","text":" respectively. This manages the keychain items for the password and refresh token, as well as storing the access token in-memory."}]},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The access token is being stored in-memory due to how frequently the token expires.","type":"text"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conforms to "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" and is the default object used for Apple platforms. It’s also the default object used when initializing with "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":". However, you’re free to create your own implementation if it doesn’t suit your needs.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"At this time, Linux and Windows developers will need to implement their own ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to achieve the same effect. However, default ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"s for those platforms will be created at a later date.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","style":"note"}]}],"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"0.21 to 0.26 Authentication Flow Migration","modules":[{"name":"ATProtoKit"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit"]]},"sections":[],"references":{"atprotokit_icon.png":{"identifier":"atprotokit_icon.png","type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/atprotokit_icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"alt":"A technology icon representing the ATProtoKit framework."},"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/ATProtocolConfiguration/authenticate(with:password:)":{"url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/atprotocolconfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","abstract":[],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"authenticate","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"with"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"text":"password","kind":"external